{"title_page": "United States presidential elections in Kansas", "text_new": "{{Infobox elections by state\n| state = Kansas\n| number_of_elections = 39\n| voted_democrat = 6\n| voted_republican = 32\n| voted_other = 1{{efn|James B. Weaver, 1892.}}\n| voted_winning = 27\n| voted_losing = 12\n}}\t\nFollowing is a table of '''United States presidential elections in Kansas''', ordered by year. Since its admission to statehood in 1861, [[Kansas]] has participated in every U.S. presidential election. As of 2017, Kansas has the longest streak of being decided by more than a 5% margin in presidential elections, with the last race this close being in 1896.\n\nWinners of the state are in '''bold'''.\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Winner (nationally)\n! Votes\n! Percent\n! Loser (nationally)\n! Votes\n! Percent\n! Other national<br>candidates{{efn|For purposes of these lists, other national candidates are defined as those who won at least one electoral vote, or won at least ten percent of the vote in multiple states.}}\n! Votes\n! Percent\n! Electoral<br>Votes\n! Notes\n|-\n| [[2016 United States presidential election in Kansas|2016]] || '''[[Donald Trump]]'''<ref name=\"PV\">[[United States presidential elections in which the winner lost the popular vote|Won the electoral college while losing the popular vote]].</ref> || 671,018 || 56.16 || [[Hillary Clinton]] || 427,005 || 35.74 || \u2014 || || || 6 ||\n|-\n| [[2012 United States presidential election in Kansas|2012]] || [[Barack Obama]] || 440,726 || 37.99 || '''[[Mitt Romney]]''' || 692,634 || 59.71 || \u2014 || || || 6 ||\n|-\n| [[2008 United States presidential election in Kansas|2008]] || [[Barack Obama]] || 514,765 || 41.65 || '''[[John McCain]]''' || 699,655 || 56.61 || \u2014 || || || 6 ||\n|-\n| [[2004 United States presidential election in Kansas|2004]] || '''[[George W. Bush]]''' || 736,456 || 62.00 || [[John Kerry]] || 434,993 || 36.62 || \u2014 || || || 6 ||\n|-\n| [[2000 United States presid